
@startuml

' Classes
class Cinema {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -location: String
  -theatres: Set<Theatre>
}

class Theatre {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -capacity: int
  -seats: Set<Seat>
  -shows: Set<Show>
}

class Show {
  -id: int
  -movie: Movie
  -startTime: DateTime
  -endTime: DateTime
  -theatre: Theatre
  -copies: Set<MovieCopy>
  -reservations: Set<Reservation>
  -status: Status (Published, Cancelled)
}

class Movie {
  -id: int
  -title: String
  -duration: int
  -copies: Set<MovieCopy>
}

class MovieCopy {
  -id: int
  -location: Cinema
  -status: Status (Available, InUse, Moved)
}

class Seat {
  -id: int
  -number: int
  -row: int
  -theatre: Theatre
  -reserved: boolean
}

class Reservation {
  -id: int
  -customer: Customer
  -show: Show
  -seat: Seat
  -bookingTime: DateTime
  -paymentStatus: PaymentStatus (Pending, Completed)
  -cancellationTime: DateTime
}

class Customer {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -email: String
  -creditCard: CreditCard
  -reservations: Set<Reservation>
}

class CreditCard {
  -id: int
  -cardNumber: String
  -holderName: String
  -expirationDate: Date
  -cvv: String
}

class Offer {
  -id: int
  -fromShow: Show
  -toShow: Show
  -customer: Customer
  -createdAt: DateTime
  -expiresAt: DateTime
  -status: Status (Pending, Accepted, Expired, Declined)
}

class Ticket {
  -id: int
  -show: Show
  -seat: Seat
  -type: Type (Online, Entrance)
  -customer: Customer (optional)
  -price: double
  -issuedAt: DateTime
}

class System {
  +publishProgram(week: Week): void
  +cancelShow(show: Show): void
  +offerAlternativeSeat(reservation: Reservation): Offer
  +generateFreeTicket(customer: Customer, show: Show): Ticket
}

' Relationships
Cinema "1" --> "0..*" Theatre
Theatre "1" --> "0..*" Show
Show "1" --> "1" Movie
Movie "1" --> "0..*" MovieCopy
MovieCopy "1" --> "1" Cinema
Theatre "1" --> "0..*" Seat
Seat "1" --> "0..1" Reservation
Reservation "1" --> "1" Customer
Reservation "1" --> "1" Show
Reservation "1" --> "1" Seat
Customer "1" --> "0..*" Reservation
Customer "1" --> "0..*" Ticket
Ticket "1" --> "1" Show
Ticket "1" --> "1" Seat
Ticket "1" --> "0..1" Customer
Show "1" --> "0..*" Offer
Offer "1" --> "1" Customer
Offer "1" --> "1" Show (fromShow)
Offer "1" --> "1" Show (toShow)

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:
- `Status` is a conceptual enum used in multiple places (e.g., for `Show`, `MovieCopy`, `Offer`) and could be modeled as a separate class or just referenced directly.
- The `System` class is an abstract representation of the functionality provided by the application.
- The diagram reflects the core entities and their interactions without going into too much detail about methods unless they are explicitly mentioned in the requirement.

